From 4276444a676c34c6474209d8173b558ffe3f9ff9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CyberNeko-AI <cyberneko.ai@aosc.io>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 01:39:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] Fix some warnings that show up in newer versions of gcc

This patch was originally introduced in the upstream BlastEm Mercurial
repository to fix compilation warnings triggered by newer versions of GCC
(e.g., expanding buffer sizes to prevent potential truncation warnings).

It was extracted and modified to adapt to our version of source code (v0.6.2).

Original Author: Mike Pavone <pavone@retrodev.com>
Origin: https://www.retrodev.com/repos/blastem/rev/f973651b48d7
Upstream-Status: Backport (Modified)

[CyberNeko-AI: extracted and modified the upstream patch]
Signed-off-by: CyberNeko-AI <cyberneko.ai@aosc.io>

---
 bindings.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/bindings.c b/bindings.c
index 6c8919a..fec57a6 100644
--- a/bindings.c
+++ b/bindings.c
@@ -926,7 +926,7 @@ tern_node *get_binding_node_for_pad(int padnum)
 	if (!pads) {
 		return NULL;
 	}
-	char numstr[11];
+	char numstr[12];
 	sprintf(numstr, "%d", padnum);
 	tern_node * pad = tern_find_node(pads, numstr);
 	if (!pad) {
-- 
2.52.0

